annotation_impact.title: Annotation Impact
annotation_impact.description: A simple estimation of putative impact / deleteriousness : {HIGH, MODERATE, LOW, MODIFIER}

feature_type.title: Feature type
feature_type.description: Which type of feature is in the next field (e.g. transcript, motif, miRNA, etc.

feature_id.title: Feature ID
feature_id.description: Depending on the annotation, this may be: Transcript ID (preferably using version number), Motif ID, miRNA, ChipSeq peak, Histone mark, etc. Note: Some features may not have ID (e.g. histone marks from custom Chip-Seq experiments may not have a unique ID).

transcript_biotype.title: Transcript type
transcript_biotype.description: The bare minimum is at least a description on whether the transcript is {“Coding”, “Noncoding”}. Whenever possible, use ENSEMBL biotypes.

rank.title: Rank
rank.description: Exon or Intron rank / total number of exons or introns.

hgvs_p.title: HGVS.p
hgvs_p.description: If variant is coding, this field describes the variant using HGVS notation (Protein level). Since transcript ID is already mentioned in ‘feature ID’, it may be omitted here.

cdna_pos_cdna_length.title: cDNA.position/cNDA.length
cdna_pos_cdna_length.description: Position in cDNA and trancript’s cDNA length (one based).

cds_pos_cds_length.title: CDS.position/CDS.length
cds_pos_cds_length.description: Position and number of coding bases (one based includes START and STOP codons).

exonicfunc_ensgene.title: Exonic annotation of ENSEMBL
exonicfunc_ensgene.description: Exonic annotation of ENSEMBL if the variant is exonic

func2_ensgene.title: Annotation of ENSEMBL (exonic annotation)
func2_ensgene.description: Annotation of ENSEMBL including exonic annotation

exonicfunc_refgene.title: Exonic annotation of NCBI RefSeq
exonicfunc_refgene.description: Exonic annotation of NCBI RefSeq if the variant is exonic

exonicfunc_knowngene.title: Exonic annotation of UCSC
exonicfunc_knowngene.description: Exonic annotation of UCSC if the variant is exonic
